The next Full Moon is on March 7, in the sun sign of Pisces and therefore its opposing sign of Virgo. Full Moons always bring a pause in the month to reflect, ponder, contemplate, review, and release. More thought than action. This Full Moon’s Virgo vibe draws our attention to home, health, and work. Particularly, the routines, schedules and rituals we have created around those things. Are they working? Are they rewarding? Are they efficient and easy to do? Are they a default or a struggle? Figure out what’s important to be done, automatically and regularly, around your home, health, and work, and review the processes or routines you have for doing it. Improvements, with helpful Virgo, can always be made! Let the tarot guide you towards what you need to sharpen up in your life this Full Moon… March 21 to April 20 Tarot card for Aries for the Full Moon in Virgo: The Magician Meaning: It’s important in your life to be creative, to come up with ideas, to invent new ways and means of doing things, to innovate and be progressive. Are you set up to do that? Do you know when you’re at your most creative and do you schedule that work then? Do you know how to stimulate out-the-box thinking in yourself? Do you seek good stimulus and food for thought? Consider, because The Magician shows you can get more out if you make your creativity a priority process! Head here for everything you need to know about being an Aries April 21 to May 21 Tarot card for Taurus for the Full Moon in Virgo: The Sun Meaning: You are a pleasure seeker but sometimes you forget to really plan your downtime, you just sort of drift into it and often end up on the couch, not doing much, maybe feeling like you’ve wasted your time off. The Sun urges you to schedule your fun! Plan for it. Look for things you really want to do and spread them out over the coming weeks. Don’t overplan it, but do add in some structure so you make the most of the time you have to yourself. Head here for everything you need to know about being a Taurus May 22 to June 21 Tarot card for Gemini for the Full Moon in Virgo: Temperance Meaning: You tend to lean towards extremes vs finding a nice balance across your whole life. Temperance asks you to keep things in moderation and keep the variety of activity going. When you like something, don’t overdo it because you take the shine off it. When you’re committed to a project, make sure you have other things going on too or you’ll feel bored of it before too long. Don’t let your routines between one-sided or overly focused on just one thing. Keep the balance and you’ll feel energised because a change is as good as a rest for Geminis. Head here for everything you need to know about being a Gemini June 22 to July 23 Tarot card for Cancer for the Full Moon in Virgo: The Hermit Meaning: You need more quality time alone. Not for brooding, sleeping, or dwelling on old wounds (although, if you must, then do so…) but for concentration, research, personal development, enlightenment and investment in your own self. The Hermit asks you to get serious about what you do with your alone time – make it count, make it valuable, make it have a purpose. Use reading, podcasts, meditation, creativity, research, and puzzles to stimulate your mind, have ideas, learn, process things, come up with inspirations. Put down the remote control and pick up your journal! Head here for everything you need to know about being a Cancer July 24 to August 23 Tarot card for Leo for the Full Moon in Virgo: Nine of Cups Meaning: The Nine of Cups is a nudge that you might not be putting enough focus and structured work into achieving and moving closer to your most heartfelt wish right now. Leo, it won’t happen by itself! Dreams can come true but that requires traction and action. You need to make it happen. You need to treat this like a project, not a fantasy, and create a plan of attack. Take this more seriously and start putting the effort in because you can do it. Head here for everythi