to be made. Now. Head here for everything you need to know about being a Scorpio November 23 to December 21 Tarot card for Sagittarius for the Full Moon in Virgo: Three of Swords Meaning: You are acting in a slightly distorted way to avoid pressing on a wound that you’re fiercely protective of. Someone or something has hurt you deeply and the pain is intense. This is making you over-react, be super defensive, push back in OTT ways… and that is actually hurting you (and others) even more. The system has broken. Take a break. Breathe. Process. Heal. The Three of Swords asks you to put blame where it’s owed and nowhere else. Don’t make yourself, or others, pay. Don’t create new problems. Focus on healing your emotional wound and getting back to normal. Head here for everything you need to know about being a Sagittarius December 22 to January 21 Tarot card for Capricorn for the Full Moon in Virgo: King of Coins Meaning: The King of Coins is you to a tee – practical, wealthy, ambitious, successful, go-getting. You are on the make this Full Moon, looking at stepping up your game in work and wealth-creation. In fact, you’d like to take on a more leadership or entrepreneurial outlook or role. This is the time to plan your strategy, create a vision, research your tactics to get ahead and get what you deserve. Promotion, investment, creation. You are intent on making your own luck in this life and it starts here. Head here for everything you need to know about being a Capricorn January 22 to February 19 Tarot card for Aquarius for the Full Moon in Virgo: Two of Swords Meaning: This Full Moon, face into your biggest and most tricky life decision. Get it all out on the table, pick it apart, deconstruct the options and consequences, mitigate the risks, pressure test your thinking, get feedback. This decision is the key to unlocking your momentum right now and, until you make it, you will keep on circling the same old ground. The Two of Swords brings clarity, honesty, and courage